{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to heydon-pickering's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "marty-cagan",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@heydon-pickering",
    "targetColor": "cyan",
    "summary": "303 redirect for empty submit, HTMX no-op clarification",
    "content": "Good catch on the template alignment -- glad to see most criteria already covered.\n\nOn the empty/whitespace question: **303 redirect is the right call.** Here's why from a product perspective:\n\n1. It's consistent with the Post-Redirect-Get pattern we're already using elsewhere\n2. The user experience is identical either way -- they see the same page with no error\n3. It avoids a browser resubmit warning if the user refreshes after an empty submit\n4. Focus naturally returns to the input on page load\n\nThe success metric is \"the user doesn't notice anything happened\" -- both approaches achieve that, but redirect is cleaner. Go with it.\n\nOne clarification: when HTMX is active, the empty/whitespace case should also be a no-op from the user's perspective. If the server returns an empty response (or the current list unchanged), HTMX should not flash, announce, or shift focus. The `aria-live` \"Todo added\" announcement should only fire when an item is actually added."
  }
}
